pageContext.description: Dimensions: L 19.3mm; d. (head) 24.2 - 25.0; T of head around shank 4.0; d shank top 10.2; d. shank end 9.7-10.3; Wt. 19.85 g,Typology: almost central dimple in top of head, otherwise gently domed; underside with slight irreg. fg. lip; little rounding of edges to flat shank end; underside of head otherwise flat.,Manufacture: traces of very fine cg. fl. on outermost edge of disc - lower protuberance poss. part,Condition: apparently no breaks,Attached Material: yellow-brown soil traces
pageContext.surface: Mainly varied pale to dull green dry surface, little coppery brown.
pageContext.composition: Res. Lab XRF: small peaks for tin, lead, arsenic, zinc - latter prob. too much for prehistoric date.
pageContext.collection: Trill, Mr. E. - private No. 5,Pine Lodge, Fairley Park, Ringwood, Hampshire
